Base call barplot

To evaluate base changes standard MAF fields were summarized as two new variables: The base_change variable indicates the exact change in bases from concatenating Reference_Allele, >, and Allele. The change variable is made from the base_change variable but groups together deletions, insertions, and long (more than a SNV) as their own groups.

Read depth and VAF

Compare read depth and VAF calculations.

vaf = (t_alt_count) / (t_ref_count + t_alt_count)

This is following the code used in maftools. The VAF calculations and other special variables are added to the MAF fields and written to a TSV ending in _vaf.tsv in the caller’s results folder.

Genomic regional analyses

To analyze what genomic regions the variants are from, Annotatr package hg38 genome annotations were used. Mutations are assigned all annotations that they overlap (using GenomicRanges::overlap).

Percent variants in COSMIC

The COSMIC mutation data used here are the full, unfiltered somatic mutations from CosmicMutantExport.tsv, grch38. COSMIC mutations are overlapped with the present data’s mutations using GenomicRanges. The mutations that overlap with COSMIC mutations are plotted here.

TMB by histology

To calculate TMB, the sum of the bases (in Mb) included in the WXS or WGS BED regions are used as the denominator, depending on the sample’s processing strategy.

TMBwxs = sum(mutation_w-in_bedwxs)/(wxs_genome_size/1000000)
TMBwgs = sum(all_mutations)/(wgs_genome_size/1000000)

BED regions used for WGS samples are caller specific, while the WXS samples are calculated using the same BED file for all.
